@NODE "shell" "shell"
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B}@{U} @{JCENTER} Upload via Shell ...@{UB} @{uu}
@{JCENTER}
GoogleTool has a simple shell interface, so that is possible to upload films to youtube via Shell.
 This is useful so you can google tool integrated into a file type of Ambient.

Operation:

GoogleTool USER/A, PASSWORD/A, NAME/A, PATH/A:

USER: User name of the Google access. This is usually your own email address.

PASSWORD: The password for the Google access.

NAME: The name of a film that is used by Youtube to manage.

PATH: Local file path to the movie file to be uploaded.


@Endnode

@NODE "app" app "
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B}@{U} @{JCENTER} Drop movies...@{UB} @{uu}
@{JCENTER}
GoogleTool has the App Window functionality. It may invite all downloadable movies
by letting them fall on the window. Also, several of the same
be dropped. All films end up in the film list of GoogleTool.
@Endnode

@NODE "on" "concerning"
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B}@{U} @{JCENTER} About...@{UB} @{uu}
@{JCENTER}
GoogleTool can upload movies to YouTube and download maps from Google Maps.
@Endnode

@NODE "lad" "lad"
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B} @{U} @{JCENTER} What can it load ...@{UB} @{uu}
@{JCENTER}
For Youtube: MPEG-1, MPEG-2, MPEG-4, Mp4, Avi.
@Endnode

@NODE "spc" "spc"
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B} @{U} @{JCENTER} What can it save...@{UB} @{uu}
@{JCENTER}
From GoogleMaps: Png.
@Endnode

@NODE "prt" "prt"
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B} @{U} @{JCENTER} What can it print ...@{UB} @{uu}
@{JCENTER}
From GoogleMaps: GoogleTool print nativly on a laser printer with Postscript emulation.
Turbo Print is only supported if, because in this case, the handler Gohstscript
can switch between.
@Endnode

@NODE "bra" bra "
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B} @{U} @{JCENTER} What does it need  ...@{UB} @{uu}
@{JCENTER}
It requires MorphOS> = 2.7,
100 MB Ram,
Monitor with at least 1024x768
@Endnode

@Node "up" "up"
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B}@{U} @{JCENTER} Upload to Youtube ...@{UB} @{uu}
It's easy:
"Throw" a movie file on the GoogleTool-window,
click the entry of the movie,
writes in the text entry box (located below the list)
any name for the movie in,
and then click "Upload"
Done!
@Endnode

@Node "down" "down"
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B}@{U} @{JCENTER} Download from Google Maps ...@{UB} @{uu}
@{JCENTER}
That's even easier ...
In the text box (located above the map display window)
you type in any city, village, address or whole
global coordinate pairs.
Now if you pressed the retrun key, either the appropriate map
downloaded.
Well, one still a possibility with two buttons Cycle
set the magnification and the type of map.
The "update" button is only needed when inter-
time e.g. changed the nature of the map without changing the address.
@Endnode

@NODE "help" "help"
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B}@{U} @{JCENTER} Help  ...@{UB} @{uu}
@{JCENTER}
Almost every button has a short help in the form of a bubble.
@Endnode

@Node "window" window "
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B} @{U} @{JCENTER} Extra window ...@{UB} @{uu}
@{JCENTER}
The menu of the window from GoogleTool has the entrys "Google" and "printer".

Google:
There, the login data is entered.

Printer:
There, the printer path is entered.
@Endnode

@NODE "project" "project"
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B}@{U} @{JCENTER} Projects ...@{UB} @{uu}
@{JCENTER}
GoogleTool can save the movie list for Youtube and invite back.
@Endnode

@NODE "more" important "
@TOC "main"
@PREV "main"
@{B} @{U} @{JCENTER} Important ...@{UB} @{uu}
@{JCENTER}
About the google maps - access with GoogleTool, you can only
1000 maps download per day.
If someone more downloading, the IP is blocked on google maps for a short time.
Permanently this limit is exceeded, the IP is blocked permanently.
@Endnode






